# Supabase DB and RLS

- Any DB schema change must include a migration in `supabase/migrations`.
- Never modify production DB directly as a substitute for migrations.
- Preserve RLS safety and review policy impact before changing data access.
- Never expose service role usage to client-side code.
- Keep user visibility and `app_access_status` rules safe.
- Consider indexes for new query patterns.
- Update TypeScript types and services when schema changes.
- Mention migration status and commit requirements in the final response.
